Acting Armed Forces chief of staff Jose Calimlim told reporters that he received a lot of inquiries from foreign ambassadors based in Manila asking about the condition of the hostages.
The Sulu hostages were seized by Filipino gunmen in a diving resort of Sipadan in Sabah, Malaysia and brought them over to Talipao, Sulu two days later.
The hostages are being guarded by about 40 to 50 gunmen in talipao in the southern philippine island province of sulu.
Calimlim noted that government soldiers have sealed off the area to prevent the kidnappers from escaping.
